      "id": "w_db3523def8c7c_19dfc6ef2b4",
      "title": "Cuore Blu",
      "artist": "Sebastien Boulard",
      "year": "2025",
      "description": "Cuore Blu showcases the largest wave ever surfed in the Mediterranean while delving into Simone Macera's personal bond with the sea. The film also explores the diverse ways in which others, including local elders, relate to the sea, offering a mosaic of perspectives on this vital element.\nBased in Livorno, Italy, Simone’s story is one shaped by the many interpretations of the sea. For some, it’s a space for sunbathing; for others, it’s about fishing, sailing, or surfing. Yet, despite these varied pursuits, the sea ultimately serves as a place of profound self-reconnection, a place where one can reconnect with their true self, away from the distractions of modern life.",
