      "title": "The Rites of Man",
      "artist": "Fred Sprinkle",
      "year": "2025",
      "description": "Time-traveling anthropologists document the heartbreak of an aspiring entrepreneur and his discovery of an alien substance living inside him.\nThe Rites of Man is a work of poetic existential philosophy, inspired by the work of Byung-Chul Han, Simone Weil, Hannah Arendt, and Zygmunt Bauman. It plumbs questions of motivation and meaning in the 21st century: what forces drive our hustle for success in this technological world we’ve created.",
